CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1773191771
OL,3,CHealth and education systems
OL,4,C'underperforming' says think tank
OL,6,FFive years after the height of the
OL,7,Fpandemic, waiting lists for planned
OL,8,FNHS treatment in Wales have begun to
OL,9,Ffall. However, they remain higher than
OL,10,Fbefore COVID-19 and have taken longer
OL,11,Fto start declining than in England.
OL,12,FMeanwhile, waiting times in accident
OL,13,Fand emergency departments have
OL,14,Fcontinued to worsen.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1773191771
OL,3,CHealth and education systems
OL,4,C'underperforming' says think tank
OL,6,FAccording to the analysis, the median
OL,7,Fwaiting time for elective treatment in
OL,8,FWales stood at 19 weeks in December
OL,9,F2025. This is almost double the pre-
OL,10,Fpandemic level of 10.7 weeks and
OL,11,Faround 40% longer than the comparable
OL,12,Fwaiting time in England.
OL,14,FPerformance in emergency departments
OL,15,Fhas also struggled according to the
OL,16,FIFS. In December 2025, only 53% of
OL,17,Fpatients spent less than four hours in
OL,18,Fmajor A&E departments, far below the
OL,19,Fofficial target of 95%.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1773191771
OL,3,CHealth and education systems
OL,4,C'underperforming' says think tank
OL,6,FAverage hospital stays are also around
OL,7,F40% longer in Wales than in England,
OL,8,Freducing the number of patients
OL,9,Fhospitals can admit and treat.
OL,11,FResearchers say the reasons for the
OL,12,Fgap are not fully clear but suggested
OL,13,Fthat policy decisions and how services
OL,14,Fare delivered may play a role.
OL,16,FIn education, school absence rates
OL,17,Fremain much higher than before COVID-
OL,18,F19. During the 2024`25 academic year,
OL,19,Faround 9% of pupils in Wales were
OL,20,Fabsent on any given day, compared with
OL,21,Fless than 6% in 2019.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1773191771
OL,3,CHealth and education systems
OL,4,C'underperforming' says think tank
OL,6,FPersistent absence has risen even more
OL,7,Fsharply. The proportion of pupils
OL,8,Fmissing more than 10% of school
OL,9,Fsessions increased from 15% in 2019 to
OL,10,F34% in 2025.
OL,12,FPerformance in the internationally
OL,13,Fcomparable Programme for International
OL,14,FStudent Assessment (PISA) tests has
OL,15,Falso declined more in Wales than in
OL,16,FEngland since the pandemic, widening
OL,17,Fthe attainment gap between the two
OL,18,Fcountries.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
